        <article id="text" class="section-wrapper clearfix" data-custom-background-img="assets/images/other_images/bg1.jpg">
          <div class="content-wrapper clearfix">
            <div class="col-sm-10 col-md-9 pull-right">

                <h1 class="section-title">Who I Am</h1>

                <p class="feature-paragraph">
<!--<img data-img-src="assets/images/other_images/transp-image5b.png" class="lazy pull-right" alt="Jon Lind: Who I Am">-->

<h4>Philosophy</h4>
	<p>An innate desire to say "yes".  An almost obsession with performance and efficiency and trying to achieve maximum productivity.  </p>
	<p>Honesty, openness, transparency and authenticity.  Let's embrace opportunities and challenges openly and head-on.  And you'll never hear an excuse from me.</p>
	<p>A real commitment and pride in the quality of my work, and an ability to learn from those around me to constantly improve while mentoring and pushing the team to do the same.</p>
	<p>The ability to build strong relationships with all of the disciplines that go into a successful project, from product owners, designers, architects and engineers to quality assurance and project management.</p>

<h4>Experience</h4>
Helping to start-up a small Internet Service Provider in the mid-90s I quickly transitioned to building websites, databases, secure e-commerce solutions, mobile apps and designing and building the infrastructure to support it all.  I have worked with <a href="#portfolio">some of the highest traffic sites on the web</a>, keenly understanding the importance of designing a solution that is reliable, can scale, and is flexible enough to grow and change to support the organization for years to come. 
</p>
<h4>Passion</h4>
<p>Having developed software since I was twelve years old it is a life-long passion and I have had the great fortune to be able to devote my career to learning and mentoring the technology of the web.  Bringing this experience to people and organizations to avoid the mistakes of the past and come up with the best solutions for the future is deeply satisfying.  
</p>
            </div><!-- .col-sm-10 -->
          </div><!-- .content-wrapper -->
        </article><!-- .section-wrapper -->

